[{"tags": [], "vote": 0, "age": null, "language": "en", "bookmarked": false, "permanent": false, "page_rating": 0, "comments": [], "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "date_published": "2024-01-24T22:52:17+00:00", "page_rating_contents": 0, "user": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/1/24/24049658/playstation-5-update-cronus-zen-blocked-cheats", "page_rating_votes": 0, "title": "PlayStation 5 update blocks Cronus Zen cheat devices", "page_rating_visits": 0, "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Sony\u2019s PS5 console.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/XhTL9Bs-aICuq3KcF6Vw6uFtToU=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73082521/vpavic_4278_20201030_0292.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo by Vjeran Pavic / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"Qu3HQB\">The PlayStation 5\u2019s latest update blocks players from using the Cronus Zen \u2014 a device cheaters use to get an unfair advantage in first-person shooters and other games \u2014 as spotted by <em>Call of Duty </em>news site <a href=\"https://twitter.com/charlieINTEL\"><em>CharlieIntel</em></a>. A notice on the <a href=\"https://www.cronusmax.com/\">Cronus website</a> warns players that the <a href=\"https://www.playstation.com/en-us/support/hardware/ps5/system-software-info/#:~:text=Version%3A%C2%A024.01%2D08.60.00\">24.01-08.60.00 update</a> for the PS5 no longer allows the Cronus Zen to connect to the console.</p>\n<p id=\"pE0tjk\">Although Cronus bills the device as a \u201ccontr", "artist": null, "source_obj__id": 61, "thumbnail": null, "album": "", "dead": false}, {"tags": [], "vote": 0, "age": null, "language": "en", "bookmarked": false, "permanent": false, "page_rating": 0, "comments": [], "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "date_published": "2024-01-24T22:16:21+00:00", "page_rating_contents": 0, "user": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/1/24/24049639/rivian-r2-ev-march-announcement-launch-laguna-beach", "page_rating_votes": 0, "title": "Rivian\u2019s R2 vehicle launch date appears to leak in town council minutes", "page_rating_visits": 0, "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Rivian R1S front \" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/tsyRMZRzKXlH36Y0nsXgqdjpo9Y=/0x0:2048x1365/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73082398/236609_Rivian_R1S_review_DGolson_008.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo by Daniel Golson for The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"3Pjsvo\">City council members in Laguna Beach, California met last night prepared to approve a request (<a href=\"https://lagunabeachcity.granicus.com/MetaViewer.php?view_id=3&amp;event_id=2629&amp;meta_id=184362\">PDF</a>) from Rivian to park six vehicles on the grass in a city park for a March 7th \u201cR2 launch.\u201d The company appears to be planning to officially announce its forthcoming electric SUV, the R2, which is supposed to be smaller and more affordable than its current lineup of EVs.</p>\n<p id=\"tNh0Sp\">A local community publication called <em>Stu News Laguna</em> <a href=\"https://stunewslaguna.com/fair-game-012324/\">reported yesterday that</a> a small it", "artist": null, "source_obj__id": 61, "thumbnail": null, "album": "", "dead": false}, {"tags": [], "vote": 0, "age": null, "language": "en", "bookmarked": false, "permanent": false, "page_rating": 0, "comments": [], "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "date_published": "2024-01-24T21:44:26+00:00", "page_rating_contents": 0, "user": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/1/24/24049436/esr-qi2-car-mount-15w-wireless-iphone-charging-mag-safe", "page_rating_votes": 0, "title": "This Qi2 car mount is cheaper than a MagSafe charger and can fast-charge your iPhone 15", "page_rating_visits": 0, "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A close-up view of the Qi2 car mount.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/HsD41RenY3laJXOwJgPT31eMIsg=/0x127:1114x870/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73082303/Screen_Shot_2024_01_24_at_12.08.31_PM.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: ESR</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"xU5Xei\">A new car mount for your smartphone just launched that offers a rare combo: Qi2 wireless charging at high speeds \u2014 and at a reasonable price. The Qi2 car mount, from accessories maker ESR, offers 15W wireless charging to fast-charge your <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/9/12/23870494/qi2-certification-iphone-15-magnetic-charging\">iPhone 15 and 15 Pro</a> at its maximum capacity while you\u2019re en route.</p>\n<p id=\"CioVA7\">With a <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0CM3DCWQY?maas=maas_adg_10B185D57979E237AE92196B7E2A17D6_afap_abs&amp;_kx=YkiYqbmRVqF5f9QXrQ-E5jwUslnH0FUlbcg0XYGI2WA%3D.JbWTAc&amp;th=1&amp;linkCode=sl1&amp;tag=rikkasama-20&amp;linkId=24", "artist": null, "source_obj__id": 61, "thumbnail": null, "album": "", "dead": false}, {"tags": [], "vote": 0, "age": null, "language": "en", "bookmarked": false, "permanent": false, "page_rating": 0, "comments": [], "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "date_published": "2024-01-24T21:29:01+00:00", "page_rating_contents": 0, "user": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/1/24/24048988/tesla-q4-earnings-revenue-margin-cybertruck", "page_rating_votes": 0, "title": "Tesla\u2019s profits improved slightly, but still down compared to last year", "page_rating_visits": 0, "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/TZjJYTpNoN27MfD_7qknjOLiQwo=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73082257/236938_Tesla_showroom_Cyber_Truck_AKrales_0251.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo by Amelia Holowaty Krales / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"cntVTN\">Tesla <a href=\"https://digitalassets.tesla.com/tesla-contents/image/upload/IR/TSLA-Q4-2023-Update.pdf\">reported earnings</a> of $7.9 billion in net income on $25.2 billion in revenue during the fourth quarter of 2023. The figures represent an increase in revenue, up from $24.3 billion the same time last year.</p>\n<p id=\"RsTt2T\">The company\u2019s profit margins improved slightly but are still down compared to last year\u2019s. The company reported margins of 8.2 percent, up slightly from 7.6 percent the previous quarter but down from last year\u2019s 16 percent. </p>\n<p id=\"Il1dY7\">Tesla used to have historic profit margins, sometimes as much as 20 percent, but a", "artist": null, "source_obj__id": 61, "thumbnail": null, "album": "", "dead": false}, {"tags": [], "vote": 0, "age": null, "language": "en", "bookmarked": false, "permanent": false, "page_rating": 0, "comments": [], "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "date_published": "2024-01-24T21:07:19+00:00", "page_rating_contents": 0, "user": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/1/24/24049478/verizon-netflix-premium-starz-deal-sale", "page_rating_votes": 0, "title": "Netflix Premium and Starz is $25.99 per month for Verizon customers", "page_rating_visits": 0, "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Illustration of the Netflix wordmark on a red and black background.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/REy3nXlmz0Urp-odnj2UYF0T65A=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73082188/STK072_VRG_Illo_N_Barclay_5_netflix.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration by Nick Barclay / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"Iqdq6p\"><a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/1/24/24049085/verizon-sees-a-future-in-streaming-bundles\">As predicted</a>, Verizon has swooped in with a new streaming bundle deal \u2014 and now that <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/1/23/24048107/netflix-basic-subscription-ads-earnings-q4-2023\">Netflix has once again</a> raised prices for some customers, this one might be worth a look. </p>\n<p id=\"YTxrTb\">Right now, Verizon customers can get Netflix Premium and Starz together for $25.99 per month, <a href=\"https://www.anrdoezrs.net/links/8532386/type/dlg/sid/verge/https://www.verizon.com/about/news/veriz", "artist": null, "source_obj__id": 61, "thumbnail": null, "album": "", "dead": false}, {"tags": [], "vote": 0, "age": null, "language": "en", "bookmarked": false, "permanent": false, "page_rating": 0, "comments": [], "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "date_published": "2024-01-24T20:53:44+00:00", "page_rating_contents": 0, "user": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/1/24/24049382/samsung-self-repair-television-foldables-projectors", "page_rating_votes": 0, "title": "Samsung is making DIY fixes easier for some of its TVs", "page_rating_visits": 0, "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"An image showing the Samsung logo on an abstract background\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/pq1aLZWWXpSoLeBXb_6YlcBikAE=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73082134/acastro_STK075_01.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration by Alex Castro / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"gtaUr9\">Samsung is <a href=\"https://news.samsung.com/us/samsung-adds-foldables-and-home-entertainment-products-to-self-repair-program/\">making parts and repair guides available for a bunch more of its devices</a>, including three sizes of this year\u2019s The Frame TV and both of its flagship foldable phones. The company says that for many of the TV and other display repairs, you\u2019ll only need simple tools like a screwdriver to make a fix happen. </p>\n<p id=\"w3EZaQ\">Samsung says DIYers will be able to replace \u201cparts related to picture, power, WiFi connection, [and] sound\u201d for various display types. Users can also buy repair guides and p", "artist": null, "source_obj__id": 61, "thumbnail": null, "album": "", "dead": false}, {"tags": [], "vote": 0, "age": null, "language": "en", "bookmarked": false, "permanent": false, "page_rating": 0, "comments": [], "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "date_published": "2024-01-24T20:36:41+00:00", "page_rating_contents": 0, "user": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/1/24/24049467/national-science-foundation-ai-research-biden-eo", "page_rating_votes": 0, "title": "Joe Biden\u2019s big AI science project gets pledges from Microsoft, Nvidia and others", "page_rating_visits": 0, "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"An image showing a repeating pattern of brain illustrations\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/421zSnW3Ybk0Yy0g1I_IifzGl9E=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73082100/acastro_181017_1777_brain_ai_0003.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration: Alex Castro / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"VZG4fO\">The National Science Foundation (NSF) and 10 other agencies are partnering with artificial intelligence developers to fulfill part of President Joe Biden\u2019s executive order on AI, launching a pilot program the administration says will democratize access to research. </p>\n<p id=\"m7rTGK\">The National Artificial Intelligence Research Resource (NAIRR) provides access to AI models, computing power, datasets, software, and training for US-based AI researchers, the NSF said in <a href=\"https://new.nsf.gov/news/democratizing-future-ai-rd-nsf-launch-national-ai\">a statement</a>. Researchers can apply for access to the ", "artist": null, "source_obj__id": 61, "thumbnail": null, "album": "", "dead": false}, {"tags": [], "vote": 0, "age": null, "language": "en", "bookmarked": false, "permanent": false, "page_rating": 0, "comments": [], "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "date_published": "2024-01-24T19:49:11+00:00", "page_rating_contents": 0, "user": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/1/24/24049445/klarna-plus-bnpl-consumer-debt-ipo", "page_rating_votes": 0, "title": "Klarna will now let you pay them so you can pay them less money", "page_rating_visits": 0, "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"An illustration of a piggy bank, a pile of cash, and some coins\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/t_c3csFZ6Y3snK4au34ZIvh2juY=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73081927/STK417_H_Herrera_Money_01.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Dollars and sense?</em> | Illustration by Hugo Herrera / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"cIYmEp\">Great news for those of you already experiencing subscription fatigue: you can subscribe to buy now, pay later (BNPL) service Klarna for $7.99 a month.</p>\n<p id=\"RuWj2U\">At first glance, this seemed pretty fucking weird to me. I mean, the entire point of Klarna is that you can essentially do layaway without paying any kind of interest; Klarna has partnered with a wide array of retailers \u2014 from Dolce &amp; Gabbana to 1-800-Flowers.com to Macy\u2019s \u2014 to create this service. So what\u2019s the consumer value in the subscription?</p>\n<div class=\"c-float-left c-float-hang\"><aside id=\"5oomxl\">", "artist": null, "source_obj__id": 61, "thumbnail": null, "album": "", "dead": false}, {"tags": [], "vote": 0, "age": null, "language": "en", "bookmarked": false, "permanent": false, "page_rating": 0, "comments": [], "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "date_published": "2024-01-24T19:27:58+00:00", "page_rating_contents": 0, "user": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/1/24/24048446/insta360-link-webcam-mobvoi-ticwatch-pro-5-tcl-qm8-mini-led-tv-deal-sale", "page_rating_votes": 0, "title": "Insta360\u2019s auto-swiveling Link webcam has fallen to its best price to date", "page_rating_visits": 0, "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Insta360 Link\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/nX6lEaLsGa-Rq974pOy7Du3jsnw=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73081848/cfaulkner_220727_5351_0001.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Who says webcams can\u2019t be fun?</em> | Photo by Cameron Faulkner / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"8Xh6Hs\">At this point, I think it\u2019s pretty safe to say that remote work is here to stay in at least some capacity, even if <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/9/5/23860073/meta-return-to-office-three-days-wfh-work-from-home\">Meta</a>, <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2022/8/15/23307268/apple-hybrid-working-model-return-to-office-september\">Apple</a>, <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2021/5/6/22422518/google-hybrid-work-office-remote-work-sundar-pichai-memo-covid-19-pandemic\">Google</a>, and a host of other companies have rolled out more stringent WFH policies over the past year. Thankfully for those of us who work from hom", "artist": null, "source_obj__id": 61, "thumbnail": null, "album": "", "dead": false}, {"tags": [], "vote": 0, "age": null, "language": "en", "bookmarked": false, "permanent": false, "page_rating": 0, "comments": [], "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "date_published": "2024-01-24T19:00:00+00:00", "page_rating_contents": 0, "user": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24047857/macintosh-40th-anniversary-apple-imac-powerbook-macbook-studio-pro-air", "page_rating_votes": 0, "title": "Looking back on 40 years of Macintosh", "page_rating_visits": 0, "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/l18yLZFLBkdQlurjY0r4SwJndi0=/0x0:1500x1000/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73081753/macs.0.jpg\" />\n    </figure>\n\n  <div id=\"wnMQlP\">\n\n    \n\n\n\n\n\n</div>\n<p id=\"QgXw9j\">The Apple we know today is far removed from the one that created the first Macintosh computer that Steve Jobs showed off in a <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2014/1/24/5340626/apple-macintosh-30th-anniversary-celebration\">very silly presentation</a> on January 24th, 1984. It\u2019s been the most valuable company in the world for most of the last decade. It has a global, meticulously curated supply chain, retail stores around the world, and near-constant <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/1/17/24041945/apple-watch-series-9-ultra-2-blood-oxygen-ban\">legal</a> and <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/1/8/23961923/apple-app-store-appeal-european-union-digital-markets-act-core-platform-service-gatekeeper\">regulatory</a> trouble. An", "artist": null, "source_obj__id": 61, "thumbnail": null, "album": "", "dead": false}, {"tags": [], "vote": 0, "age": null, "language": "en", "bookmarked": false, "permanent": false, "page_rating": 0, "comments": [], "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "date_published": "2024-01-24T18:39:01+00:00", "page_rating_contents": 0, "user": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24049147/lysfanga-the-time-shift-warrior-release-date-steam", "page_rating_votes": 0, "title": "Fight monsters with the help of your past lives in Lysfanga: The Time Shift Warrior", "page_rating_visits": 0, "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Screenshot from Lysfanga: The Time Shift Warrior featuring Ime and one of her remnants\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/-s1C-y8BXXmSqC7f_N0Na4jJ8Ow=/150x0:1770x1080/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73081712/lysfanga2.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Sand Door Games</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"18S6sm\">I distinctly remember the first time I saw <em>Lysfanga: The Time Shift Warrior</em>. It was <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/6/8/23754562/summer-game-fest-women-diversity-geoff-keighley\">during Summer Game Fest last year</a>, and the game\u2019s <a href=\"https://youtu.be/BDRfAVyW0aw\">brief minute-long reveal trailer</a> was enough to leave a lasting impression. I\u2019ve been looking forward to playing it ever since. My patience has been rewarded with the news that <em>Lysfanga: The Time Shift Warrior </em>will launch on February 13th on PC.</p>\n<div id=\"sPDs2z\"><div style=\"width: 100%; height: 0; padding-bottom: 56.25%;\"", "artist": null, "source_obj__id": 61, "thumbnail": null, "album": "", "dead": false}, {"tags": [], "vote": 0, "age": null, "language": "en", "bookmarked": false, "permanent": false, "page_rating": 0, "comments": [], "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "date_published": "2024-01-24T18:18:38+00:00", "page_rating_contents": 0, "user": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/1/24/24049165/ring-police-neighbors-app-clips-search-warrant", "page_rating_votes": 0, "title": "Ring steps back from sharing video with police \u2014 mostly", "page_rating_visits": 0, "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"An image showing a Ring doorbell on a house\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/zwNvc7shadakchRBsz_sRGM_sEY=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73081656/jtuohy_220531_5259_0018.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo by Jennifer Pattison Tuohy / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"LS5XLP\">Ring will no longer let local police publicly ask people for doorbell footage through its Neighbors app. The Amazon-owned <a href=\"https://blog.ring.com/about-ring/ring-announces-new-neighbors-app-features-sunsets-request-for-assistance-post/\">company announced</a> it\u2019s going to sunset its Request for Assistance tool this week, forcing police to obtain a warrant for most of its video requests.</p>\n<p id=\"OhPP0v\">This change might seem like a step in the right direction, but it may actually make the clip-requesting process <em>less</em> transparent, as police can <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2022/7/14/23219419/amazon-ring-l", "artist": null, "source_obj__id": 61, "thumbnail": null, "album": "", "dead": false}, {"tags": [], "vote": 0, "age": null, "language": "en", "bookmarked": false, "permanent": false, "page_rating": 0, "comments": [], "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "date_published": "2024-01-24T18:09:41+00:00", "page_rating_contents": 0, "user": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/1/24/24048458/twitch-prime-subscription-change-partner-plus-expansion", "page_rating_votes": 0, "title": "Streamers who rely on Twitch Prime Gaming subs are getting a slight pay cut", "page_rating_visits": 0, "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Twitch logo\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/Lgi4rGGpkKQZUHeq3m8mS-1zPng=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73081627/STK044_VRG_Illo_N_Barclay_3_twitch.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration by Nick Barclay / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"h6QiUg\">Twitch is making big monetization changes again in an attempt to make a more sustainable system, lowering earnings in some places and raising them in others. This new batch of changes includes expanding its Partner Plus program and changing the way its integral Twitch Prime Gaming subscription pays out creators.</p>\n<p id=\"kuTsIq\"><a href=\"https://blog.twitch.tv/en/2024/01/24/an-update-to-several-streamer-payout-programs/\">In a blog post</a>, CEO Dan Clancy outlined three major changes coming to the ways streamers make money from Twitch. </p>\n<p id=\"yUAUpB\">First, Twitch is eliminating the $100,000 cap on its 70 / 30 revenue split for the platform\u2019s hi", "artist": null, "source_obj__id": 61, "thumbnail": null, "album": "", "dead": false}, {"tags": [], "vote": 0, "age": null, "language": "en", "bookmarked": false, "permanent": false, "page_rating": 0, "comments": [], "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "date_published": "2024-01-24T18:03:56+00:00", "page_rating_contents": 0, "user": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/1/24/24049285/microsoft-3-trillion-dollar-market-valuation-milestone", "page_rating_votes": 0, "title": "Microsoft is now a $3 trillion company", "page_rating_visits": 0, "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Microsoft logo\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/wnD8ZWVLEJHk6zhb6oPdyrX560A=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73081613/STK095_Microsoft_04.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration: The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"hxs2BX\">Microsoft has reached a $3 trillion market cap, the first time in its 48-year history. It\u2019s the second company, after Apple, to reach the milestone valuation after stock in Microsoft climbed 1.5 percent in trading on the NASDAQ on Wednesday.</p>\n<p id=\"xlYEP7\">Apple first hit the $3 trillion market cap two years ago, more than a year after it surpassed the <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2020/8/19/21375223/apple-2-trillion-market-cap-first-us-company-stock-price\">$2 trillion mark in 2020</a>. Microsoft and Apple have been trading places for the world\u2019s most valuable company in recent weeks, with Microsoft <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/1/11/24034434/microsoft-apple-marke", "artist": null, "source_obj__id": 61, "thumbnail": null, "album": "", "dead": false}, {"tags": [], "vote": 0, "age": null, "language": "en", "bookmarked": false, "permanent": false, "page_rating": 0, "comments": [], "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "date_published": "2024-01-24T17:56:38+00:00", "page_rating_contents": 0, "user": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/1/24/24049047/data-center-ai-crypto-bitcoin-mining-electricity-report-iea", "page_rating_votes": 0, "title": "AI and crypto mining are driving up data centers\u2019 energy use", "page_rating_visits": 0, "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A view of a building complex surrounded by greenery and a road in the front.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/u0q7rPfr8-KvdQopaO6X0voRWkE=/612x0:2388x1184/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73081565/1258661059.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>A view of Meta\u2019s data center in Clonee Co Meath, Ireland. Picture date: Tuesday June 13, 2023.&nbsp;</em> | Photo by Niall Carson/PA Images via Getty Images</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"qrbDbg\">Data centers could gobble up twice as much electricity by 2026 thanks in large part to cryptocurrencies and artificial intelligence, according to a new <a href=\"https://www.iea.org/reports/electricity-2024\">report</a> from the International Energy Agency (IEA).</p>\n<p id=\"d7hQHv\">We rely on data centers to store all our emails, photos, cat videos, and everything else floating around in the cloud. More and more, data centers are cropping up to mine Bitcoin and train AI. </p>\n<p id=\"9xNC0L\">Tha", "artist": null, "source_obj__id": 61, "thumbnail": null, "album": "", "dead": false}, {"tags": [], "vote": 0, "age": null, "language": "en", "bookmarked": false, "permanent": false, "page_rating": 0, "comments": [], "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "date_published": "2024-01-24T17:44:14+00:00", "page_rating_contents": 0, "user": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24049212/on-stewart-daily-show-return-date", "page_rating_votes": 0, "title": "Jon Stewart\u2019s coming back to The Daily Show, but only on Mondays", "page_rating_visits": 0, "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A man in a gray suit, blue shirt, and dark blue tie. The man\u2019s sitting at a large, glossy newsdesk, and behind him is a broadcast news set featuring the image of a city skyline.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/kKFTxWvuRKdErqI5KwLDMSTCZpQ=/242x0:2639x1598/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73081508/Screen_Shot_2015-04-07_at_10.13.09_AM.0.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Comedy Central</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"TDprPB\">Just months after <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/10/19/23924549/jon-stewart-apple-ai-china-cancel\">Jon Stewart\u2019s sudden departure from Apple TV Plus</a>, the comedian is set to make his return to <em>The Daily Show </em>on Comedy Central.</p>\n<p id=\"t3JNDV\"><a href=\"https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/tv/tv-news/jon-stewart-the-daily-show-host-1235802984/\">According to <em>The Hollywood Reporter</em></a>, <em>The Daily Show</em>\u2019s yearlong search for a new host following <a href=\"https://www.hol", "artist": null, "source_obj__id": 61, "thumbnail": null, "album": "", "dead": false}, {"tags": [], "vote": 0, "age": null, "language": "en", "bookmarked": false, "permanent": false, "page_rating": 0, "comments": [], "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "date_published": "2024-01-24T17:00:00+00:00", "page_rating_contents": 0, "user": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/1/24/24048981/amie-calendar-app-ios-mac-web", "page_rating_votes": 0, "title": "Amie is a beautiful, simple calendar app with really big dreams", "page_rating_visits": 0, "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A screenshot of the Amie calendar app, showing tasks and events.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/Tk4csmQ0B7h3kI72ibFit57BGZk=/42x0:1659x1078/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73081348/desktop.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Amie does tasks and calendar side by side, which is delightful.</em> | Image: Amie</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"nUIhk5\">There\u2019s another company vying to be the place you go to manage your time. It\u2019s called <a href=\"https://amie.so/\">Amie</a>, and it\u2019s one of the best-looking calendar apps I\u2019ve used. It\u2019s available today for iOS, Mac, and the web after four years in development and many months in beta testing. I\u2019ve been using it off and on for a long time, and I like it a lot. </p>\n<p id=\"dP4Tsf\">The first thing that drew me to Amie was that it\u2019s set up to be a combination of a task list and a calendar. You have lists of tasks in the left sidebar, and you then drag tasks into the calendar to give th", "artist": null, "source_obj__id": 61, "thumbnail": null, "album": "", "dead": false}, {"tags": [], "vote": 0, "age": null, "language": "en", "bookmarked": false, "permanent": false, "page_rating": 0, "comments": [], "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "date_published": "2024-01-24T17:00:00+00:00", "page_rating_contents": 0, "user": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/1/24/24048895/microsoft-teams-microsoft-mesh-launch-vr-meetings-3d-immersive", "page_rating_votes": 0, "title": "Microsoft Teams now supports 3D and VR meetings", "page_rating_visits": 0, "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"You can roast virtual marshmallows in Microsoft\u2019s 3D meetings\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/zgcZb1mBWKgwF4iv3UVwtBoodfc=/160x0:1888x1152/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73081347/mashmallows.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Microsoft</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"FgSJhc\">Microsoft is launching its immersive 3D meetings inside Microsoft Teams today. Microsoft Mesh, the company\u2019s mixed reality platform, is coming out of preview and being integrated into Teams to let people gather in virtual spaces with or without a VR headset.</p>\n<p id=\"1bJ1N3\">I got to <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/15/23960720/microsoft-teams-microsoft-mesh-immersive-meetings-january-2024-launch\">try out Mesh inside Microsoft Teams</a> late last year, and it feels a lot like a corporate version of AltspaceVR, the social VR platform Microsoft acquired in 2017 and <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/1/21/23565188/altspace-vr-shutting-", "artist": null, "source_obj__id": 61, "thumbnail": null, "album": "", "dead": false}, {"tags": [], "vote": 0, "age": null, "language": "en", "bookmarked": false, "permanent": false, "page_rating": 0, "comments": [], "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "date_published": "2024-01-24T16:00:00+00:00", "page_rating_contents": 0, "user": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24049014/apple-epic-court-ruling-developer-tax", "page_rating_votes": 0, "title": "Apple thought it dealt with Epic v. Apple \u2014 has it really?", "page_rating_visits": 0, "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"An illustration of the App Store logo.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/VF0ClW3-XrE_7JiI8iArqzr7V38=/0x0:3000x2000/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73081148/acastro_STK045_01.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration by Alex Castro / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n\n  \t\t <p>Apple has started letting developers link to third-party payment processors, but only if it\u2019s on Apple\u2019s own terms.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24049014/apple-epic-court-ruling-developer-tax\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>", "artist": null, "source_obj__id": 61, "thumbnail": null, "album": "", "dead": false}, {"tags": [], "vote": 0, "age": null, "language": "en", "bookmarked": false, "permanent": false, "page_rating": 0, "comments": [], "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "date_published": "2024-01-24T15:00:00+00:00", "page_rating_contents": 0, "user": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24048972/palworld-news-trailers", "page_rating_votes": 0, "title": "Pok\u00e9mon with guns? All the latest on viral gaming hit Palworld", "page_rating_visits": 0, "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A screenshot from the video game Palworld.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/LQoSyie7hfme2xY0gqUgU2aVHzQ=/150x0:1770x1080/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73080876/ss_43ed640c916ec689981a74f0818e5b9c77204d1c.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Pocketpair</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p>The multiplayer survival game has become 2024\u2019s biggest surprise.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24048972/palworld-news-trailers\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>", "artist": null, "source_obj__id": 61, "thumbnail": null, "album": "", "dead": false}, {"tags": [], "vote": 0, "age": null, "language": "en", "bookmarked": false, "permanent": false, "page_rating": 0, "comments": [], "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "date_published": "2024-01-24T14:31:02+00:00", "page_rating_contents": 0, "user": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24048027/phone-accessories-case-iphone-pixel-samsung-favorite", "page_rating_votes": 0, "title": "The Verge\u2019s favorite mobile phone gadgets", "page_rating_visits": 0, "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Samsung phone with blue stand on desk.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/hiANtMNrkvpWtHBB1irz9elN-hM=/0x11:1150x778/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73080839/Screenshot_2024_01_24_at_8.30.16_AM.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Moft</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"trlHiq\">Every year, major phone manufacturers such as <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/10/30/23938867/apple-m3-imac-macbook-pro-biggest-announcements-m3\">Apple</a>, <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/23902026/google-pixel-8-launch-event-biggest-announcements-watch-buds-pro\">Google</a>, and <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/1/17/24041928/samsung-galaxy-s24-ai-event-2024\">Samsung</a> hold elaborate events meant to introduce and publicize their upcoming phones. Well, buying a new phone is all well and good, but things don\u2019t stop there. Once you\u2019ve got the phone, you have to buy yourself a case (so you won\u2019t crack that shiny new device the first time you ", "artist": null, "source_obj__id": 61, "thumbnail": null, "album": "", "dead": false}, {"tags": [], "vote": 0, "age": null, "language": "en", "bookmarked": false, "permanent": false, "page_rating": 0, "comments": [], "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "date_published": "2024-01-24T14:30:00+00:00", "page_rating_contents": 0, "user": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24048479/apple-mac-40-anniversary", "page_rating_votes": 0, "title": "The Mac turns 40 \u2014\u00a0and keeps on moving", "page_rating_visits": 0, "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/5rjV3nQ7OQSvTUywHbu20H-LaUg=/0x0:1800x1200/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73080829/party_mac.0.jpg\" />\n    </figure>\n\n  <div id=\"kWeUrS\">\n\n    \n\n\n\n\n\n</div>\n<p id=\"tiLUBO\">Twenty years ago, on the Mac\u2019s 20th anniversary, I <a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/article/169580/themacturns20jobs.html\">asked Steve Jobs</a> if the Mac would still be relevant to Apple in the age of the iPod. He scoffed at the prospect of the Mac not being important: \u201cof course\u201d it would be.</p>\n<p id=\"L8eKKv\">Yet, 10 years later, Apple\u2019s revenue was increasingly dominated by the iPhone, and the recent success of the new iPad had provided another banner product for the company. When I interviewed Apple exec Phil Schiller for the Mac\u2019s 30th anniversary, I found myself asking him about the Mac\u2019s relevance, too. <a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/article/222761/apple-executives-on-the-mac-at-30-the-mac-keeps-going-forever.ht", "artist": null, "source_obj__id": 61, "thumbnail": null, "album": "", "dead": false}, {"tags": [], "vote": 0, "age": null, "language": "en", "bookmarked": false, "permanent": false, "page_rating": 80, "comments": [], "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "date_published": "2024-01-24T14:00:00+00:00", "page_rating_contents": 80, "user": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/1/24/24048892/nvidia-rtx-video-hdr-feature-ai", "page_rating_votes": 0, "title": "Nvidia\u2019s RTX GPUs can now upgrade SDR content to HDR using AI", "page_rating_visits": 3, "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Nvidia\u2019s logo.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/Zq9H84THS5p0P7OOoy04MqdWfiU=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73080733/acastro_STK083_01.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration by Alex Castro / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"m9WtGI\">Nvidia is launching a new feature for all RTX GPU owners today: RTX Video HDR. Much like how <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/2/28/23618245/nvidia-rtx-video-super-resolution-upscale-videos-rtx-gpu\">Nvidia\u2019s RTX Video Super Resolution</a> can upscale old, blurry web videos, RTX Video HDR uses AI to convert SDR color space video to HDR. You just need an HDR10